originalText.text: I went into this branch recently to pick up some bank checks - I was about to sign the lease for my dream apartment, and I was so nervous and had no idea what I was doing as I'd never had to get bank checks before. I was helped by Paul who patiently and kindly explained what I needed to know and do; not only did he get me everything I needed efficiently and accurately, but I also left feeling a lot calmer and more organized, confident, and knowledgeable about my banking process. Thank you!!

originalText.text:
The entire process of find a TD location with a representative or even a hotline representative had been literally the hardest banking experience. I have called over 15 locations and went to a physical open location in harlem, turned away due to limited services... was going to give up until i found paul at madison. he deserves this review.

- i had decided to go with TD over BOA based on a bonus offer for my small business
- opened account online but couldn't finish depositing money
- debit card mailed to my house
- no access to my account number over the phone to receive account info
- therefore don't know if i actually made an account
- therefore can't deposit money unless in an actual branch
- therefore worried about it billing me fees for not depositing money
- feeling out of time and increased anxiety due to unable to walk in an actual branch at the moment

called the madison branch as last resort and if this too shall fail, i will give up on TD.
- to my surprise, paul answered instead of a voicemail like countless times before
- spoken with absolute clarity and patience
- answered all of my questions and provided extra solutions and insight
- reassured me on deadlines and requirements
- friendly and understanding, no rushing
- ended the call feeling extremely satisfied with the service and compelled to write this review to highlight his capabilities

This is EXCELLENCE!
if he's not a manager or upper position, he deserves to be.

üôè
